    <note>Tian(1) Zhiping [21594] He was the younger brother of Zhian [21593], first adopted heir of Kuang [1617], whose son, Dan [21595] (or Xuan), became the second adopted heir of Kuang. Kuang was buried in Xuzhou, Yangdi (modern Yuxian) and Xuan (Dan) is identified as a Yuxian resident. Kuang may, or may not have moved to Yuxian, probably the unnamed brother who was father of Zhian and Zhiping made the move. See documentation for Kuang (particularly funerary inscription by Fan Chunren and funerary inscription for wife, born Fu(6), by Fan Zuyu).</note>
